Package com.poesys.accounting.dataloader.oldaccounting

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    OldDataBuilder.IBuildStrategy
    Strategy pattern that allows the Builder to share the basic file-reading code, putting the construction-specific work into each strategy class.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractReaderDto
    Abstract superclass for DTOs initialized by reading lines from a Reader
    Account
    Data transfer object for old-accounting Account data.
    AccountGroup
    Data transfer object representing old-accounting account group data; groups the accounts into categories like Cash or Accounts Receivable by grouping the account numbers into ranges.
    AccountMap
    Data transfer object for the account mapping data, which maps a fiscal year account number to a new-accounting account name, enabling the data loader to map accounts in any given fiscal year to the accumulating set of accounts that span fiscal years in the new accounting system; there are 2 data fields, account number and account name
    Balance
    A data transfer object containing an initial balance for the system.
    CapitalEntity
    Represents one of potentially several entities that participate in the capital structure of the accounting entity.
    Item
    A concrete DTO holding data for an item, one element of a transaction identified by the year, the transaction id, and the account.
    OldDataBuilder
    Production implementation of the IBuilder interface that loads data from a designated path for a list of fiscal years.
    Receivable
    A data transfer object that holds raw data for a receivable item, essentially tagging an existing item identified by year, transaction id, and account as a receivable item; the amount is a negative dollar amount representing a debit on the receivables account; the receivable account number must be between 110.0 and 119.99.
    Reimbursement
    A data transfer object that holds raw data for a reimbursement item; used to construct the old accounting reimbursement item object and to link up to receivables; the amounts are positive, representing credits to the receivables account.
    Transaction
    Data transfer object for old-accounting transaction data; includes the items for the transaction, loaded separately; contains a factory method that generates the new-accounting transaction data transfer object corresponding to the old-accounting transaction; fields: transaction id (Integer), description (string enclosed by double quotes with trailing blanks), transaction date (format dd-MON-yy), checked (boolean Y/N)
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EndOfStream
    Exception indicating a BufferedReader has reached the end of the input stream
